194template <class T>
195class Local {
196 public:
197 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(nullptr) {}
198 template <class S>
199 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
200 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
206 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
207 }
208
212 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
213
217 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = nullptr; }
218
219 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
220
221 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
222
233 template <class S>
234 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
235 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
236 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
237 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
238 if (b == nullptr) return false;
239 return *a == *b;
240 }
241
242 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
243 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
244 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
245 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
246 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
247 if (b == nullptr) return false;
248 return *a == *b;
249 }
250
261 template <class S>
262 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
263 return !operator==(that);
264 }
265
266 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
267 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
268 return !operator==(that);
269 }
270
276 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
277#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
278 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
279 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
280 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
281#endif
282 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
283 }
284
290 template <class S>
291 V8_INLINE Local<S> As() const {
292 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
293 }
294
300 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
301 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
302 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
303 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
304 const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that);
305
306 private:
307 friend class Utils;
308 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
309 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
310 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
311 template<class F> friend class Local;
312 template <class F>
313 friend class MaybeLocal;
314 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
315 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
316 friend class String;
317 friend class Object;
318 friend class Context;
319 friend class Isolate;
320 friend class Private;
321 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
322 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
323 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
324 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
325 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
326 friend class HandleScope;
327 friend class EscapableHandleScope;
328 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
329 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
330 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
331 template <class F>
332 friend class ReturnValue;
333 template <class F>
334 friend class Traced;
335 template <class F>
336 friend class TracedGlobal;
337 template <class F>
338 friend class TracedReferenceBase;
339 template <class F>
340 friend class TracedReference;
341
342 explicit V8_INLINE Local(T* that) : val_(that) {}
343 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
344 T* val_;
345};

365template <class T>
366class MaybeLocal {
367 public:
368 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
369 template <class S>
370 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
371 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
372 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
373 }
374
375 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
376
381 template <class S>
382 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
383 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
384 return !IsEmpty();
385 }
386
391 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
392
397 template <class S>
398 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
399 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
400 }
401
402 private:
403 T* val_;
404};

410template <class T> class Eternal {
411 public:
412 V8_INLINE Eternal() : val_(nullptr) {}
413 template <class S>
414 V8_INLINE Eternal(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) : val_(nullptr) {
415 Set(isolate, handle);
416 }
417 // Can only be safely called if already set.
418 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const;
419 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
420 template<class S> V8_INLINE void Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle);
421
422 private:
423 T* val_;
424};

427static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
428static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
429
430template <typename T>
431class WeakCallbackInfo {
432 public:
433 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
434
435 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
436 void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
437 Callback* callback)
438 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
439 for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
440 embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
441 }
442 }
443
444 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
445 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
446 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
447
448 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
449 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
450 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
451 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
452 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
453 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
454 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
455
456 private:
457 Isolate* isolate_;
458 T* parameter_;
459 Callback* callback_;
460 void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
461};
462
463
464// kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
465// will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
466// will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
467// actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
468// possible to request a second pass callback.
469enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };
470
484template <class T> class PersistentBase {
485 public:
490 V8_INLINE void Reset();
495 template <class S>
496 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
497
502 template <class S>
503 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& other);
504
505 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
506 V8_INLINE void Empty() { val_ = 0; }
507
508 V8_INLINE Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
509 return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this);
510 }
511
512 template <class S>
513 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
514 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
515 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
516 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
517 if (b == nullptr) return false;
518 return *a == *b;
519 }
520
521 template <class S>
522 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
523 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
524 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
525 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
526 if (b == nullptr) return false;
527 return *a == *b;
528 }
529
530 template <class S>
531 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
532 return !operator==(that);
533 }
534
535 template <class S>
536 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
537 return !operator==(that);
538 }
539
552 template <typename P>
553 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
554 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
555 WeakCallbackType type);
556
564 V8_INLINE void SetWeak();
565
566 template<typename P>
567 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
568
569 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
570 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }
571
578 V8_INLINE void AnnotateStrongRetainer(const char* label);
579
581 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
582
586 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
587
592 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
593
594 PersistentBase(const PersistentBase& other) = delete; // NOLINT
595 void operator=(const PersistentBase&) = delete;
596
597 private:
598 friend class Isolate;
599 friend class Utils;
600 template<class F> friend class Local;
601 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
602 template <class F>
603 friend class Global;
604 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
605 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
606 template <class F1, class F2, class F3>
607 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
608 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;
609 friend class Object;
610
611 explicit V8_INLINE PersistentBase(T* val) : val_(val) {}
612 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
613
614 T* val_;
615};

624template<class T>
625class NonCopyablePersistentTraits {
626 public:
627 typedef Persistent<T, NonCopyablePersistentTraits<T> > NonCopyablePersistent;
628 static const bool kResetInDestructor = false;
629 template<class S, class M>
630 V8_INLINE static void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
631 NonCopyablePersistent* dest) {
632 static_assert(sizeof(S) < 0,
633 "NonCopyablePersistentTraits::Copy is not instantiable");
634 }
635};
636
637
642template<class T>
643struct CopyablePersistentTraits {
644 typedef Persistent<T, CopyablePersistentTraits<T> > CopyablePersistent;
645 static const bool kResetInDestructor = true;
646 template<class S, class M>
647 static V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M>& source,
648 CopyablePersistent* dest) {
649 // do nothing, just allow copy
650 }
651};

662template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
663 public:
667 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
673 template <class S>
674 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
675 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
676 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
677 }
683 template <class S, class M2>
684 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
685 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
686 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
687 }
694 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
695 Copy(that);
696 }
697 template <class S, class M2>
698 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
699 Copy(that);
700 }
701 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
702 Copy(that);
703 return *this;
704 }
705 template <class S, class M2>
706 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
707 Copy(that);
708 return *this;
709 }
715 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
716 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
717 }
718
719 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
720 template <class S>
721 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
722#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
723 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
724 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
725 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
726#endif
727 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
728 }
729
730 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
731 template <class S>
732 V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
733 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
734 }
735
736 private:
737 friend class Isolate;
738 friend class Utils;
739 template<class F> friend class Local;
740 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
741 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
742
743 explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
744 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
745 template<class S, class M2>
746 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
747};

843template <typename T>
844class TracedReferenceBase {
845 public:
850 bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
851
856 V8_INLINE void Reset();
857
861 Local<T> Get(Isolate* isolate) const { return Local<T>::New(isolate, *this); }
862
863 template <class S>
864 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& that) const {
865 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
866 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
867 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
868 if (b == nullptr) return false;
869 return *a == *b;
870 }
871
872 template <class S>
873 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
874 internal::Address* a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_);
875 internal::Address* b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
876 if (a == nullptr) return b == nullptr;
877 if (b == nullptr) return false;
878 return *a == *b;
879 }
880
881 template <class S>
882 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& that) const {
883 return !operator==(that);
884 }
885
886 template <class S>
887 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
888 return !operator==(that);
889 }
890
894 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
895
900 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;
901
902 template <class S>
903 V8_INLINE TracedReferenceBase<S>& As() const {
904 return reinterpret_cast<TracedReferenceBase<S>&>(
905 const_cast<TracedReferenceBase<T>&>(*this));
906 }
907
908 protected:
912 void SetSlotThreadSafe(T* new_val) {
913 reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<T*>*>(&val_)->store(new_val,
914 std::memory_order_relaxed);
915 }
916
920 const T* GetSlotThreadSafe() const {
921 return reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<const T*> const*>(&val_)->load(
922 std::memory_order_relaxed);
923 }
924
925 private:
926 enum DestructionMode { kWithDestructor, kWithoutDestructor };
927
931 TracedReferenceBase() = default;
932
933 V8_INLINE static T* New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
934 DestructionMode destruction_mode);
935
936 T* val_ = nullptr;
937
938 friend class EmbedderHeapTracer;
939 template <typename F>
940 friend class Local;
941 friend class Object;
942 template <typename F>
943 friend class TracedGlobal;
944 template <typename F>
945 friend class TracedReference;
946 template <typename F>
947 friend class ReturnValue;
948};

1147
1151 template <class S>
1152 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(TracedReference<S>&& rhs);
1153
1157 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference& rhs);
1158
1162 template <class S>
1163 V8_INLINE TracedReference& operator=(const TracedReference<S>& rhs);
1164
1169 template <class S>
1170 V8_INLINE void Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other);
1171
1172 template <class S>
1173 V8_INLINE TracedReference<S>& As() const {
1174 return reinterpret_cast<TracedReference<S>&>(
1175 const_cast<TracedReference<T>&>(*this));
1176 }
1177
1182 bool IsEmptyThreadSafe() const {
1183 return this->GetSlotThreadSafe() == nullptr;
1184 }
1185};

1225 internal::Address value);

1229 // Therefore declare them private instead to disable dynamic alloc
1230 void* operator new(size_t size);
1231 void* operator new[](size_t size);
1232 void operator delete(void*, size_t);
1233 void operator delete[](void*, size_t);
1234
1235 internal::Isolate* isolate_;

1237 internal::Address* prev_limit_;

1240 template<class F> friend class Local;

1243 // a HeapObject in their shortcuts.
1244 friend class Object;
1245 friend class Context;
1246};

1392class ScriptOriginOptions {
1393 public:
1394 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1395 bool is_opaque = false, bool is_wasm = false,
1396 bool is_module = false)
1397 : flags_((is_shared_cross_origin ? kIsSharedCrossOrigin : 0) |
1398 (is_wasm ? kIsWasm : 0) | (is_opaque ? kIsOpaque : 0) |
1399 (is_module ? kIsModule : 0)) {}
1400 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1401 : flags_(flags &
1402 (kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque | kIsWasm | kIsModule)) {}
1403
1404 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1405 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1406 }
1407 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1408 bool IsWasm() const { return (flags_ & kIsWasm) != 0; }
1409 bool IsModule() const { return (flags_ & kIsModule) != 0; }
1410
1411 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1412
1413 private:
1414 enum {
1415 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1,
1416 kIsOpaque = 1 << 1,
1417 kIsWasm = 1 << 2,
1418 kIsModule = 1 << 3
1419 };
1420 const int flags_;
1421};

1696class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1697 public:
1705 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1706 enum BufferPolicy {
1707 BufferNotOwned,
1708 BufferOwned
1709 };
1710
1711 CachedData()
1712 : data(nullptr),
1713 length(0),
1714 rejected(false),
1715 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1716
1717 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1718 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1719 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1720 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1721 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1722 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1723 ~CachedData();
1724 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1725 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1726 const uint8_t* data;
1727 int length;
1728 bool rejected;
1729 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1730
1731 // Prevent copying.
1732 CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;
1733 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&) = delete;
1734 };
1735
1739 class Source {
1740 public:
1741 // Source takes ownership of CachedData.
1742 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string, const ScriptOrigin& origin,
1743 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1744 V8_INLINE Source(Local<String> source_string,
1745 CachedData* cached_data = nullptr);
1746 V8_INLINE ~Source();
1747
1748 // Ownership of the CachedData or its buffers is *not* transferred to the
1749 // caller. The CachedData object is alive as long as the Source object is
1750 // alive.
1751 V8_INLINE const CachedData* GetCachedData() const;
1752
1753 V8_INLINE const ScriptOriginOptions& GetResourceOptions() const;
1754
1755 // Prevent copying.
1756 Source(const Source&) = delete;
1757 Source& operator=(const Source&) = delete;
1758
1759 private:
1760 friend class ScriptCompiler;
1761
1762 Local<String> source_string;
1763
1764 // Origin information
1765 Local<Value> resource_name;
1766 Local<Integer> resource_line_offset;
1767 Local<Integer> resource_column_offset;
1768 ScriptOriginOptions resource_options;
1769 Local<Value> source_map_url;
1770 Local<PrimitiveArray> host_defined_options;
1771
1772 // Cached data from previous compilation (if a kConsume*Cache flag is
1773 // set), or hold newly generated cache data (kProduce*Cache flags) are
1774 // set when calling a compile method.
1775 CachedData* cached_data;
1776 };

2254// A StateTag represents a possible state of the VM.
2255enum StateTag {
2256 JS,
2257 GC,
2258 PARSER,
2259 BYTECODE_COMPILER,
2260 COMPILER,
2261 OTHER,
2262 EXTERNAL,
2263 ATOMICS_WAIT,
2264 IDLE
2265};

2267// A RegisterState represents the current state of registers used
2268// by the sampling profiler API.
2269struct RegisterState {
2270 RegisterState() : pc(nullptr), sp(nullptr), fp(nullptr), lr(nullptr) {}
2271 void* pc; // Instruction pointer.
2272 void* sp; // Stack pointer.
2273 void* fp; // Frame pointer.
2274 void* lr; // Link register (or nullptr on platforms without a link register).
2275};
2276
2277// The output structure filled up by GetStackSample API function.
2278struct SampleInfo {
2279 size_t frames_count; // Number of frames collected.
2280 StateTag vm_state; // Current VM state.
2281 void* external_callback_entry; // External callback address if VM is
2282 // executing an external callback.
2283 void* top_context; // Incumbent native context address.
2284};

3754 // Implements CreateDataProperty (ECMA-262, 7.3.4).
3755 //
3756 // Defines a configurable, writable, enumerable property with the given value
3757 // on the object unless the property already exists and is not configurable
3758 // or the object is not extensible.
3759 //
3760 // Returns true on success.

3770 // In general, CreateDataProperty will be faster, however, does not allow
3771 // for specifying attributes.

3775 Local<Context> context, Local<Name> key, Local<Value> value,
3776 PropertyAttribute attributes = None);
3777
3778 // Implements Object.DefineProperty(O, P, Attributes), see Ecma-262 19.1.2.4.
3779 //
3780 // The defineProperty function is used to add an own property or
3781 // update the attributes of an existing own property of an object.
3782 //
3783 // Both data and accessor descriptors can be used.
3784 //
3785 // In general, CreateDataProperty is faster, however, does not allow
3786 // for specifying attributes or an accessor descriptor.
3787 //
3788 // The PropertyDescriptor can change when redefining a property.
3789 //
3790 // Returns true on success.
3791 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT Maybe<bool> DefineProperty(

4289template<typename T>
4290class ReturnValue {
4291 public:
4292 template <class S> V8_INLINE ReturnValue(const ReturnValue<S>& that)
4293 : value_(that.value_) {
4294 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
4295 }
4296 // Local setters
4297 template <typename S>
4298 V8_INLINE void Set(const Global<S>& handle);
4299 template <typename S>
4300 V8_INLINE void Set(const TracedReferenceBase<S>& handle);
4301 template <typename S>
4302 V8_INLINE void Set(const Local<S> handle);
4303 // Fast primitive setters
4304 V8_INLINE void Set(bool value);
4305 V8_INLINE void Set(double i);
4306 V8_INLINE void Set(int32_t i);
4307 V8_INLINE void Set(uint32_t i);
4308 // Fast JS primitive setters
4309 V8_INLINE void SetNull();
4310 V8_INLINE void SetUndefined();
4311 V8_INLINE void SetEmptyString();
4312 // Convenience getter for Isolate
4313 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const;
4314
4315 // Pointer setter: Uncompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse.
4316 template <typename S>
4317 V8_INLINE void Set(S* whatever);
4318
4319 // Getter. Creates a new Local<> so it comes with a certain performance
4320 // hit. If the ReturnValue was not yet set, this will return the undefined
4321 // value.
4322 V8_INLINE Local<Value> Get() const;
4323
4324 private:
4325 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
4326 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
4327 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
4328 template <class F, class G, class H>
4329 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
4330 V8_INLINE void SetInternal(internal::Address value) { *value_ = value; }
4331 V8_INLINE internal::Address GetDefaultValue();
4332 V8_INLINE explicit ReturnValue(internal::Address* slot);
4333 internal::Address* value_;
4334};

6647struct NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration {
6648 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6649 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
6650 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
6651 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query,
6652 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
6653 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
6654 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
6655 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
6656 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6657 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6658 : getter(getter),
6659 setter(setter),
6660 query(query),
6661 deleter(deleter),
6662 enumerator(enumerator),
6663 definer(definer),
6664 descriptor(descriptor),
6665 data(data),
6666 flags(flags) {}
6667
6668 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6670 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter = nullptr,
6671 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter = nullptr,
6672 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query = nullptr,
6673 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter = nullptr,
6674 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator = nullptr,
6675 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6676 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6677 : getter(getter),
6678 setter(setter),
6679 query(query),
6680 deleter(deleter),
6681 enumerator(enumerator),
6682 definer(nullptr),
6683 descriptor(nullptr),
6684 data(data),
6685 flags(flags) {}
6686
6687 NamedPropertyHandlerConfiguration(
6688 GenericNamedPropertyGetterCallback getter,
6689 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter,
6690 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor,
6691 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter,
6692 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator,
6693 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer,
6694 Local<Value> data = Local<Value>(),
6695 PropertyHandlerFlags flags = PropertyHandlerFlags::kNone)
6696 : getter(getter),
6697 setter(setter),
6698 query(nullptr),
6699 deleter(deleter),
6700 enumerator(enumerator),
6701 definer(definer),
6702 descriptor(descriptor),
6703 data(data),
6704 flags(flags) {}
6705

6707 GenericNamedPropertySetterCallback setter;
6708 GenericNamedPropertyQueryCallback query;
6709 GenericNamedPropertyDeleterCallback deleter;
6710 GenericNamedPropertyEnumeratorCallback enumerator;
6711 GenericNamedPropertyDefinerCallback definer;
6712 GenericNamedPropertyDescriptorCallback descriptor;
6713 Local<Value> data;
6714 PropertyHandlerFlags flags;
6715};

7025class V8_EXPORT Extension { // NOLINT
7026 public:
7027 // Note that the strings passed into this constructor must live as long
7028 // as the Extension itself.
7029 Extension(const char* name, const char* source = nullptr, int dep_count = 0,
7030 const char** deps = nullptr, int source_length = -1);
7031 virtual ~Extension() { delete source_; }
7032 virtual Local<FunctionTemplate> GetNativeFunctionTemplate(
7033 Isolate* isolate, Local<String> name) {
7034 return Local<FunctionTemplate>();
7035 }
7036
7037 const char* name() const { return name_; }
7038 size_t source_length() const { return source_length_; }
7039 const String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source() const {
7040 return source_;
7041 }
7042 int dependency_count() const { return dep_count_; }
7043 const char** dependencies() const { return deps_; }
7044 void set_auto_enable(bool value) { auto_enable_ = value; }
7045 bool auto_enable() { return auto_enable_; }
7046
7047 // Disallow copying and assigning.
7048 Extension(const Extension&) = delete;
7049 void operator=(const Extension&) = delete;
7050
7051 private:
7052 const char* name_;
7053 size_t source_length_; // expected to initialize before source_
7054 String::ExternalOneByteStringResource* source_;
7055 int dep_count_;
7056 const char** deps_;
7057 bool auto_enable_;
7058};

7083class V8_EXPORT ResourceConstraints {
7084 public:
7103 void ConfigureDefaultsFromHeapSize(size_t initial_heap_size_in_bytes,
7104 size_t maximum_heap_size_in_bytes);
7105
7115 void ConfigureDefaults(uint64_t physical_memory,
7116 uint64_t virtual_memory_limit);
7117
7121 uint32_t* stack_limit() const { return stack_limit_; }
7122 void set_stack_limit(uint32_t* value) { stack_limit_ = value; }
7123
7128 size_t code_range_size_in_bytes() const { return code_range_size_; }
7129 void set_code_range_size_in_bytes(size_t limit) { code_range_size_ = limit; }
7130
7138 size_t max_old_generation_size_in_bytes() const {
7139 return max_old_generation_size_;
7140 }
7141 void set_max_old_generation_size_in_bytes(size_t limit) {
7142 max_old_generation_size_ = limit;
7143 }
7144
7150 size_t max_young_generation_size_in_bytes() const {
7151 return max_young_generation_size_;
7152 }
7153 void set_max_young_generation_size_in_bytes(size_t limit) {
7154 max_young_generation_size_ = limit;
7155 }
7156
7157 size_t initial_old_generation_size_in_bytes() const {
7158 return initial_old_generation_size_;
7159 }
7160 void set_initial_old_generation_size_in_bytes(size_t initial_size) {
7161 initial_old_generation_size_ = initial_size;
7162 }
7163
7164 size_t initial_young_generation_size_in_bytes() const {
7165 return initial_young_generation_size_;
7166 }
7167 void set_initial_young_generation_size_in_bytes(size_t initial_size) {
7168 initial_young_generation_size_ = initial_size;
7169 }
7170
7174 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use code_range_size_in_bytes.")
7175 size_t code_range_size() const { return code_range_size_ / kMB; }
7176 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use set_code_range_size_in_bytes.")
7177 void set_code_range_size(size_t limit_in_mb) {
7178 code_range_size_ = limit_in_mb * kMB;
7179 }
7180 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use max_young_generation_size_in_bytes.")
7181 size_t max_semi_space_size_in_kb() const;
7182 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use set_max_young_generation_size_in_bytes.")
7183 void set_max_semi_space_size_in_kb(size_t limit_in_kb);
7184 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use max_old_generation_size_in_bytes.")
7185 size_t max_old_space_size() const { return max_old_generation_size_ / kMB; }
7186 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Use set_max_old_generation_size_in_bytes.")
7187 void set_max_old_space_size(size_t limit_in_mb) {
7188 max_old_generation_size_ = limit_in_mb * kMB;
7189 }
7190 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Zone does not pool memory any more.")
7191 size_t max_zone_pool_size() const { return max_zone_pool_size_; }
7192 V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("Zone does not pool memory any more.")
7193 void set_max_zone_pool_size(size_t bytes) { max_zone_pool_size_ = bytes; }
7194
7195 private:
7196 static constexpr size_t kMB = 1048576u;
7197 size_t code_range_size_ = 0;
7198 size_t max_old_generation_size_ = 0;
7199 size_t max_young_generation_size_ = 0;
7200 size_t max_zone_pool_size_ = 0;
7201 size_t initial_old_generation_size_ = 0;
7202 size_t initial_young_generation_size_ = 0;
7203 uint32_t* stack_limit_ = nullptr;
7204};

7746 size_t code_and_metadata_size_;
7747 size_t bytecode_and_metadata_size_;
7748 size_t external_script_source_size_;
7749
7750 friend class Isolate;
7751};
7752
7758struct JitCodeEvent {
7759 enum EventType {
7760 CODE_ADDED,
7761 CODE_MOVED,
7762 CODE_REMOVED,
7763 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7764 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7765 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7766 };
7767 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7768 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7769 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7770 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7771 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7772 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7773
7774 // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7775 // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7776 // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7777 // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7778 // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7779 // function.
7780 enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7781
7782 // Type of event.
7783 EventType type;
7784 CodeType code_type;
7785 // Start of the instructions.
7786 void* code_start;
7787 // Size of the instructions.
7788 size_t code_len;
7789 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7790 Local<UnboundScript> script;
7791 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7792 // code line information which is returned from the
7793 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7794 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7795 void* user_data;
7796
7797 struct name_t {
7798 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7799 // zero-terminated.
7800 const char* str;
7801 // Number of chars in str.
7802 size_t len;
7803 };
7804
7805 struct line_info_t {
7806 // PC offset
7807 size_t offset;
7808 // Code position
7809 size_t pos;
7810 // The position type.
7811 PositionType position_type;
7812 };
7813
7814 struct wasm_source_info_t {
7815 // Source file name.
7816 const char* filename;
7817 // Length of filename.
7818 size_t filename_size;
7819 // Line number table, which maps offsets of JITted code to line numbers of
7820 // source file.
7821 const line_info_t* line_number_table;
7822 // Number of entries in the line number table.
7823 size_t line_number_table_size;
7824 };
7825
7826 wasm_source_info_t* wasm_source_info;
7827
7828 union {
7829 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
7830 struct name_t name;
7831
7832 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
7833 struct line_info_t line_info;
7834
7835 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
7836 void* new_code_start;
7837 };
7838
7839 Isolate* isolate;
7840};
7841
7847enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7848 // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7849 // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7850 // Throughput may be throttled.
7851 PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7852 // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7853 // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7854 // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7855 PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7856 // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7857 // in this mode.
7858 PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7859 // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7860 // turn off latency optimizations.
7861 PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7862};
7863
7867enum JitCodeEventOptions {
7868 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
7869 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
7870 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
7871};

8085 * to tracing phases. Embedders should trade off when increments are reported
8086 * as V8 may consult global heuristics on whether to trigger garbage
8087 * collection on this change.
8088 */

8094 * is not attached to any v8::Isolate.
8095 */
8096 v8::Isolate* isolate() const { return isolate_; }
8097
8098 protected:

10000template <class T>
10001class Maybe {
10002 public:
10003 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
10004 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
10005
10009 V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
10010
10015 V8_INLINE void Check() const {
10016 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10017 }
10018
10023 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
10024 if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
10025 return IsJust();
10026 }
10027
10032 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
10033 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
10034 return value_;
10035 }
10036
10041 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
10042 return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
10043 }
10044
10045 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10046 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
10047 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
10048 }
10049
10050 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10051 return !operator==(other);
10052 }
10053
10054 private:
10055 Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
10056 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
10057
10058 bool has_value_;
10059 T value_;
10060
10061 template <class U>
10062 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10063 template <class U>
10064 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
10065};
10066
10067template <class T>
10068inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
10069 return Maybe<T>();
10070}
10071
10072template <class T>
10073inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
10074 return Maybe<T>(t);
10075}
10076
10077// A template specialization of Maybe<T> for the case of T = void.
10078template <>
10079class Maybe<void> {
10080 public:
10081 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !is_valid_; }
10082 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return is_valid_; }
10083
10084 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
10085 return IsJust() == other.IsJust();
10086 }
10087
10088 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
10089 return !operator==(other);
10090 }
10091
10092 private:
10093 struct JustTag {};
10094
10095 Maybe() : is_valid_(false) {}
10096 explicit Maybe(JustTag) : is_valid_(true) {}
10097
10098 bool is_valid_;
10099
10100 template <class U>
10101 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
10102 friend Maybe<void> JustVoid();
10103};
10104
10105inline Maybe<void> JustVoid() { return Maybe<void>(Maybe<void>::JustTag()); }

10756// --- Implementation ---
10757
10758template <class T>
10759Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that) {
10760 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10761}
10762
10763template <class T>
10764Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
10765 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10766}
10767
10768template <class T>
10769Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, const TracedReferenceBase<T>& that) {
10770 return New(isolate, that.val_);
10771}
10772
10773template <class T>
10774Local<T> Local<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10775 if (that == nullptr) return Local<T>();
10776 T* that_ptr = that;
10777 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that_ptr);
10778 return Local<T>(reinterpret_cast<T*>(HandleScope::CreateHandle(
10779 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), *p)));
10780}
10781
10782
10783template<class T>
10784template<class S>
10785void Eternal<T>::Set(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> handle) {
10786 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10787 val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10788 V8::Eternalize(isolate, reinterpret_cast<Value*>(*handle)));
10789}
10790
10791template <class T>
10792Local<T> Eternal<T>::Get(Isolate* isolate) const {
10793 // The eternal handle will never go away, so as with the roots, we don't even
10794 // need to open a handle.
10795 return Local<T>(val_);
10796}
10797
10798
10799template <class T>
10800Local<T> MaybeLocal<T>::ToLocalChecked() {
10801 if (V8_UNLIKELY(val_ == nullptr)) V8::ToLocalEmpty();
10802 return Local<T>(val_);
10803}
10804
10805
10806template <class T>
10807void* WeakCallbackInfo<T>::GetInternalField(int index) const {
10808#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10809 if (index < 0 || index >= kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback) {
10810 V8::InternalFieldOutOfBounds(index);
10811 }
10812#endif
10813 return embedder_fields_[index];
10814}
10815
10816
10817template <class T>
10818T* PersistentBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that) {
10819 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
10820 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10821 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(
10822 V8::GlobalizeReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate),
10823 p));
10824}
10825
10826
10827template <class T, class M>
10828template <class S, class M2>
10829void Persistent<T, M>::Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) {
10830 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10831 this->Reset();
10832 if (that.IsEmpty()) return;
10833 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that.val_);
10834 this->val_ = reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::CopyGlobalReference(p));
10835 M::Copy(that, this);
10836}
10837
10838template <class T>
10839bool PersistentBase<T>::IsWeak() const {
10840 typedef internal::Internals I;
10841 if (this->IsEmpty()) return false;
10842 return I::GetNodeState(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)) ==
10843 I::kNodeStateIsWeakValue;
10844}
10845
10846
10847template <class T>
10848void PersistentBase<T>::Reset() {
10849 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
10850 V8::DisposeGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_));
10851 val_ = nullptr;
10852}
10853

10855template <class T>
10856template <class S>
10857void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
10858 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10859 Reset();
10860 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10861 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
10862}

10865template <class T>
10866template <class S>
10867void PersistentBase<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate,
10868 const PersistentBase<S>& other) {
10869 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10870 Reset();
10871 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10872 this->val_ = New(isolate, other.val_);
10873}

10876template <class T>
10877template <typename P>
10878V8_INLINE void PersistentBase<T>::SetWeak(
10879 P* parameter, typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
10880 WeakCallbackType type) {
10881 typedef typename WeakCallbackInfo<void>::Callback Callback;
10882#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
10883#pragma GCC diagnostic push
10884#pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-function-type"
10885#endif
10886 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_), parameter,
10887 reinterpret_cast<Callback>(callback), type);
10888#if (__GNUC__ >= 8) && !defined(__clang__)
10889#pragma GCC diagnostic pop
10890#endif
10891}
10892
10893template <class T>
10894void PersistentBase<T>::SetWeak() {
10895 V8::MakeWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10896}
10897
10898template <class T>
10899template <typename P>
10900P* PersistentBase<T>::ClearWeak() {
10901 return reinterpret_cast<P*>(
10902 V8::ClearWeak(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_)));
10903}

10906void PersistentBase<T>::AnnotateStrongRetainer(const char* label) {
10907 V8::AnnotateStrongRetainer(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_),
10908 label);
10909}

10911template <class T>
10912void PersistentBase<T>::SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id) {
10913 typedef internal::Internals I;
10914 if (this->IsEmpty()) return;
10915 internal::Address* obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
10916 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
10917 *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr) = class_id;
10918}

10921template <class T>
10922uint16_t PersistentBase<T>::WrapperClassId() const {
10923 typedef internal::Internals I;
10924 if (this->IsEmpty()) return 0;
10925 internal::Address* obj = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(this->val_);
10926 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + I::kNodeClassIdOffset;
10927 return *reinterpret_cast<uint16_t*>(addr);
10928}
10929
10930template <class T>
10931Global<T>::Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) {
10932 if (other.val_ != nullptr) {
10933 V8::MoveGlobalReference(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&other.val_),
10934 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10935 other.val_ = nullptr;
10936 }
10937}
10938
10939template <class T>
10940template <class S>
10941Global<T>& Global<T>::operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) {
10942 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10943 if (this != &rhs) {
10944 this->Reset();
10945 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
10946 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
10947 V8::MoveGlobalReference(
10948 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
10949 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
10950 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
10951 }
10952 }
10953 return *this;
10954}
10955
10956template <class T>
10957T* TracedReferenceBase<T>::New(Isolate* isolate, T* that, void* slot,
10958 DestructionMode destruction_mode) {
10959 if (that == nullptr) return nullptr;
10960 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(that);
10961 return reinterpret_cast<T*>(V8::GlobalizeTracedReference(
10962 reinterpret_cast<internal::Isolate*>(isolate), p,
10963 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(slot),
10964 destruction_mode == kWithDestructor));
10965}
10966
10967template <class T>
10968void TracedReferenceBase<T>::Reset() {
10969 if (IsEmpty()) return;
10970 V8::DisposeTracedGlobal(reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(val_));
10971 SetSlotThreadSafe(nullptr);
10972}
10973
10974template <class T>
10975template <class S>
10976void TracedGlobal<T>::Reset(Isolate* isolate, const Local<S>& other) {
10977 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10978 Reset();
10979 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
10980 this->val_ = this->New(isolate, other.val_, &this->val_,
10981 TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithDestructor);
10982}

10984template <class T>
10985template <class S>
10986TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(TracedGlobal<S>&& rhs) {
10987 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10988 *this = std::move(rhs.template As<T>());
10989 return *this;
10990}

10993template <class S>
10994TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(const TracedGlobal<S>& rhs) {
10995 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
10996 *this = rhs.template As<T>();
10997 return *this;
10998}

11000template <class T>
11001TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(TracedGlobal&& rhs) {
11002 if (this != &rhs) {
11003 V8::MoveTracedGlobalReference(
11004 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&rhs.val_),
11005 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11006 }
11007 return *this;
11008}
11009
11010template <class T>
11011TracedGlobal<T>& TracedGlobal<T>::operator=(const TracedGlobal& rhs) {
11012 if (this != &rhs) {
11013 this->Reset();
11014 if (rhs.val_ != nullptr) {
11015 V8::CopyTracedGlobalReference(
11016 reinterpret_cast<const internal::Address* const*>(&rhs.val_),
11017 reinterpret_cast<internal::Address**>(&this->val_));
11018 }
11019 }
11020 return *this;
11021}

11026 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11027 this->Reset();
11028 if (other.IsEmpty()) return;
11029 this->SetSlotThreadSafe(
11030 this->New(isolate, other.val_, &this->val_,
11031 TracedReferenceBase<T>::kWithoutDestructor));
11032}

11105 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, S>::value, "type check");
11106 if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {
11107 *value_ = GetDefaultValue();
11108 } else {
11109 *value_ = *reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(*handle);
11110 }

11117 if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {
11118 *value_ = GetDefaultValue();

11122}

11128 "type check");
11129 if (V8_UNLIKELY(handle.IsEmpty())) {

11131 } else {

11136template<typename T>
11137void ReturnValue<T>::Set(double i) {
11138 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Number>::value, "type check");
11139 Set(Number::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11140}
11141
11142template<typename T>
11143void ReturnValue<T>::Set(int32_t i) {
11144 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11145 typedef internal::Internals I;
11146 if (V8_LIKELY(I::IsValidSmi(i))) {
11147 *value_ = I::IntToSmi(i);
11148 return;
11149 }
11150 Set(Integer::New(GetIsolate(), i));
11151}
11152
11153template<typename T>
11154void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
11155 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Integer>::value, "type check");
11156 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
11157 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
11158 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
11159 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
11160 return;
11161 }
11162 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
11163}
11164
11165template<typename T>
11166void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
11167 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Boolean>::value, "type check");
11168 typedef internal::Internals I;
11169 int root_index;
11170 if (value) {
11171 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
11172 } else {
11173 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
11174 }
11175 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
11176}
11177
11178template<typename T>
11179void ReturnValue<T>::SetNull() {
11180 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11181 typedef internal::Internals I;
11182 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kNullValueRootIndex);
11183}
11184
11185template<typename T>
11186void ReturnValue<T>::SetUndefined() {
11187 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, Primitive>::value, "type check");
11188 typedef internal::Internals I;
11189 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kUndefinedValueRootIndex);
11190}
11191
11192template<typename T>
11193void ReturnValue<T>::SetEmptyString() {
11194 static_assert(std::is_base_of<T, String>::value, "type check");
11195 typedef internal::Internals I;
11196 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11197}
11198
11199template <typename T>
11200Isolate* ReturnValue<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11201 // Isolate is always the pointer below the default value on the stack.
11202 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&value_[-2]);
11203}
11204
11205template <typename T>
11206Local<Value> ReturnValue<T>::Get() const {
11207 typedef internal::Internals I;
11208 if (*value_ == *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), I::kTheHoleValueRootIndex))
11209 return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11210 return Local<Value>::New(GetIsolate(), reinterpret_cast<Value*>(value_));
11211}
11212
11213template <typename T>
11214template <typename S>
11215void ReturnValue<T>::Set(S* whatever) {
11216 static_assert(sizeof(S) < 0, "incompilable to prevent inadvertent misuse");
11217}
11218
11219template <typename T>
11220internal::Address ReturnValue<T>::GetDefaultValue() {
11221 // Default value is always the pointer below value_ on the stack.
11222 return value_[-1];
11223}
11224
11225template <typename T>
11226FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::FunctionCallbackInfo(internal::Address* implicit_args,
11227 internal::Address* values,
11228 int length)
11229 : implicit_args_(implicit_args), values_(values), length_(length) {}
11230
11231template<typename T>
11232Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::operator[](int i) const {
11233 // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11234 if (i < 0 || length_ <= i) return Local<Value>(*Undefined(GetIsolate()));
11235#ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11236 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ + i));
11237#else
11238 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(values_ - i));
11239#endif
11240}
11241
11242
11243template<typename T>
11244Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::This() const {
11245 // values_ points to the first argument (not the receiver).
11246#ifdef V8_REVERSE_JSARGS
11247 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ - 1));
11248#else
11249 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(values_ + 1));
11250#endif
11251}
11252
11253
11254template<typename T>
11255Local<Object> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Holder() const {
11256 return Local<Object>(reinterpret_cast<Object*>(
11257 &implicit_args_[kHolderIndex]));
11258}
11259
11260template <typename T>
11261Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::NewTarget() const {
11262 return Local<Value>(
11263 reinterpret_cast<Value*>(&implicit_args_[kNewTargetIndex]));
11264}
11265
11266template <typename T>
11267Local<Value> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Data() const {
11268 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(&implicit_args_[kDataIndex]));
11269}
11270
11271
11272template<typename T>
11273Isolate* FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::GetIsolate() const {
11274 return *reinterpret_cast<Isolate**>(&implicit_args_[kIsolateIndex]);
11275}
11276
11277
11278template<typename T>
11279ReturnValue<T> FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::GetReturnValue() const {
11280 return ReturnValue<T>(&implicit_args_[kReturnValueIndex]);
11281}
11282
11283
11284template<typename T>
11285bool FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::IsConstructCall() const {
11286 return !NewTarget()->IsUndefined();
11287}
11288
11289
11290template<typename T>
11291int FunctionCallbackInfo<T>::Length() const {
11292 return length_;
11293}

11404
11405Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
11406#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11407 typedef internal::Address A;
11408 typedef internal::Internals I;
11409 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11410 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11411 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11412 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11413 if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11414 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11415 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
11416 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11417 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
11418#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
11419 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
11420 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
11421 value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
11422#endif
11423 internal::Isolate* isolate =
11424 internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
11425 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
11426 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
11427 }
11428#endif
11429 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
11430}
11431
11432
11433void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
11434#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11435 typedef internal::Address A;
11436 typedef internal::Internals I;
11437 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
11438 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
11439 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
11440 auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
11441 if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
11442 instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
11443 instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
11444 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
11445 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11446 A value = I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, offset);
11447 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(value);
11448 }
11449#endif
11450 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
11451}

11453String* String::Cast(v8::Value* value) {
11454#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11455 CheckCast(value);
11456#endif
11457 return static_cast<String*>(value);
11458}

11460
11461Local<String> String::Empty(Isolate* isolate) {
11462 typedef internal::Address S;
11463 typedef internal::Internals I;
11464 I::CheckInitialized(isolate);
11465 S* slot = I::GetRoot(isolate, I::kEmptyStringRootIndex);
11466 return Local<String>(reinterpret_cast<String*>(slot));
11467}
11468
11469
11470String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
11471 typedef internal::Address A;
11472 typedef internal::Internals I;
11473 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11474
11475 ExternalStringResource* result;
11476 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
11477 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11478 A value =
11479 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11480 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
11481 } else {
11482 result = GetExternalStringResourceSlow();
11483 }
11484#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11485 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
11486#endif
11487 return result;
11488}
11489
11490
11491String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
11492 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
11493 typedef internal::Address A;
11494 typedef internal::Internals I;
11495 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11496 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
11497 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
11498 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource;
11499 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
11500 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
11501 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(obj);
11502 A value =
11503 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
11504 resource = reinterpret_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
11505 } else {
11506 resource = GetExternalStringResourceBaseSlow(encoding_out);
11507 }
11508#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11509 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
11510#endif
11511 return resource;
11512}

11518#else

11520#endif

11522
11523bool Value::QuickIsUndefined() const {
11524 typedef internal::Address A;
11525 typedef internal::Internals I;
11526 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11527 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11528 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11529 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kUndefinedOddballKind);
11530}

11545 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11546 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11547 return (I::GetOddballKind(obj) == I::kNullOddballKind);

11550bool Value::IsNullOrUndefined() const {
11551#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
11552 return FullIsNull() || FullIsUndefined();
11553#else
11554 return QuickIsNullOrUndefined();
11555#endif
11556}
11557
11558bool Value::QuickIsNullOrUndefined() const {
11559 typedef internal::Address A;
11560 typedef internal::Internals I;
11561 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11562 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11563 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) != I::kOddballType) return false;
11564 int kind = I::GetOddballKind(obj);
11565 return kind == I::kNullOddballKind || kind == I::kUndefinedOddballKind;
11566}

11576bool Value::QuickIsString() const {

11578 typedef internal::Internals I;
11579 A obj = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
11580 if (!I::HasHeapObjectTag(obj)) return false;
11581 return (I::GetInstanceType(obj) < I::kFirstNonstringType);
11582}

11959template <typename T>
11960bool PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::ShouldThrowOnError() const {
11961 typedef internal::Internals I;
11962 if (args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] !=
11963 I::IntToSmi(I::kInferShouldThrowMode)) {
11964 return args_[kShouldThrowOnErrorIndex] != I::IntToSmi(I::kDontThrow);
11965 }
11966 return v8::internal::ShouldThrowOnError(
11967 reinterpret_cast<v8::internal::Isolate*>(GetIsolate()));
11968}

12023template <class T>
12024MaybeLocal<T> Isolate::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index) {

12026 if (data) internal::PerformCastCheck(data);
12027 return Local<T>(data);
12028}
12029
12030Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
12031#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12032 typedef internal::Address A;
12033 typedef internal::Internals I;
12034 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12035 A embedder_data =
12036 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12037 int value_offset =
12038 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12039 A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
12040#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
12041 // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
12042 // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
12043 value =
12044 I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<uint32_t>(value));
12045#endif
12046 internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
12047 *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
12048 A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
12049 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
12050#else
12051 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
12052#endif
12053}
12054
12055
12056void* Context::GetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(int index) {
12057#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
12058 typedef internal::Address A;
12059 typedef internal::Internals I;
12060 A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
12061 A embedder_data =
12062 I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
12063 int value_offset =
12064 I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
12065 internal::Isolate* isolate = I::GetIsolateForHeapSandbox(ctx);
12066 return reinterpret_cast<void*>(
12067 I::ReadExternalPointerField(isolate, embedder_data, value_offset));
12068#else
12069 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromEmbedderData(index);
12070#endif
12071}
12072
12073template <class T>
12074MaybeLocal<T> Context::GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(size_t index) {
12075 T* data = reinterpret_cast<T*>(GetDataFromSnapshotOnce(index));
12076 if (data) internal::PerformCastCheck(data);
12077 return Local<T>(data);
12078}

12084 return AddData(context, *p);
12085}

12090 internal::Address* p = reinterpret_cast<internal::Address*>(object_ptr);
12091 return AddData(*p);
12092}
